  "prompt": "How do reliance fresh or ondoor or other retail outsets who buy their products from farmers or small artisans show their valid purchase proof or invoice of goods?",
  "response": "Retail outlets like Reliance Fresh, Ondoor, and others typically manage their purchases from farmers and small artisans through the following documentation and proof of purchase methods:\n\n1. Purchase Invoice/Bill\n- Detailed invoice with:\n- Seller's details\n- Purchase date\n- Product description\n- Quantity\n- Rate\n- Total amount\n- GST details\n- Unique invoice number\n\n2. Digital Documentation\n- Electronic purchase records\n- Computerized billing systems\n- Digital signatures\n- Cloud-based transaction tracking\n\n3. Farmer/Vendor Registration\n- Formal vendor registration process\n- Unique vendor identification number\n- Documented supplier agreements\n- KYC (Know Your Customer) documentation\n\n4. Accounting Systems\n- Enterprise Resource Planning (ERP) software\n- Integrated accounting and inventory management\n- Automated purchase tracking\n- Reconciliation records\n\n5. Payment Proofs\n- Bank transfer records\n- Digital payment receipts\n- Cheque records\n- Electronic payment confirmations\n\n6. Quality/Quantity Verification\n- Receiving notes\n- Quality inspection reports\n- Goods receipt documentation\n\n7. Compliance Requirements\n- Maintaining tax-compliant records\n- GST documentation\n- Statutory record-keeping\n\nThese methods ensure transparent, traceable, and legally compliant purchasing processes.",
